{"title_page": "Civicus", "text_new": "{{COI|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox organization\n| name = CIVICUS: World Alliance For Citizen Participation\n| native_name = <!-- Organization's name in its local language -->\n| image = \n| image_size = 300px\n| motto = \n| type = International Non-profit/ Civil Society Organisation<br />INGO/CSO\n| headquarters = [[Johannesburg]], [[South Africa]]\n| services = Membership Alliance\n| leader_title = [[Secretary General]]\n| leader_name = Lysa John\n| homepage = {{URL|civicus.org}}\n}}\n\n\n'''CIVICUS''' is an international non-profit organisation, which describes itself as \u201ca global alliance dedicated to strengthening citizen action and [[civil society]] around the world.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=2014 CIVICUS Annual Report|url=http://civicus.org/AGMSecure/downloads/Annual%20Report_final%20version_sml_2.pdf#page=5|publisher=CIVICUS|accessdate=7 December 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170915034823/http://civicus.org/AGMSecure/downloads/Annual%20Report_final%20version_sml_2.pdf#page=5|archive-date=15 September 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> Founded in 1993, the organisation today counts more than 8500 members in more than 175 countries, with its headquarters in [[Johannesburg]] and offices in Geneva and New York.<ref>{{cite news|title=Calls for Azerbaijan to end crackdown on civil society and uphold Council of Europe Commitments|url=http://www.civicsolidarity.org/article/1033/calls-azerbaijan-end-crackdown-civil-society-and-uphold-council-europe-commitments|accessdate=7 December 2014|publisher=Civic Solidarity}}</ref>\n\n==Brief history==\nIn 1991, an international group of 20 leaders from [[Non governmental organisations|Non-Governmental Organisations (NGOs)]] and social movements met to explore how to support citizen participation in governmental decision-making processes.<ref>{{cite news|title=Getting a world alliance started \u2013 my four years at CIVICUS|url=http://www.alliancemagazine.org/feature/getting-a-world-alliance-started-my-four-years-at-civicus/|accessdate=7 December 2014|publisher=Alliance Magazine}}</ref> This process culminated in 1993 when a founding board established CIVICUS from the Latin term meaning \"of the community\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Reaching across sectors and building bridges|url=http://www.pdac.ca/docs/default-source/publications---communique/reaching-across-sectors-and-building-bridges-(december-2012).pdf?sfvrsn=0|website=www.pdac.ca/|publisher=Prospectors and Developers Association of Canada|accessdate=7 December 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140412112818/http://www.pdac.ca/docs/default-source/publications---communique/reaching-across-sectors-and-building-bridges-(december-2012).pdf?sfvrsn=0|archive-date=12 April 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Mission and Values==\nThe organisation works to protect and grow [[civic space]] where people can express and organise themselves.<ref>{{cite web|title=CIVICUS Our Strategic Priorities 2013- 2017|url=http://civicus.org/images/stories/CIVICUS%20SPs.English.Final.pdf|website=civicus.org/|publisher=CIVICUS|accessdate=7 December 2014}}</ref> In particular, the organisation focuses on regions where [[participatory democracy]] and [[freedom of association]] are at risk.<ref>{{cite web|title=Volunteering and Social Activism|url=http://www.unv.org/fileadmin/img/wvw/latestVolpub.pdf|website=www.unv.org/|publisher=United Nations Volunteers Organisation|accessdate=7 December 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303205556/http://www.unv.org/fileadmin/img/wvw/latestVolpub.pdf|archive-date=3 March 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> CIVICUS counts among its central values: Justice and Equality, where all people are free to exercise their rights as citizens as defined in the [[Universal Declaration of Human Rights]].<ref>{{cite book|title=International Encyclopaedia of Civil Society|publisher=Springer|url=https://www.springer.com/social+sciences/book/978-0-387-93994-0|accessdate=7 December 2014|isbn=9780387939940|date=2009-12-16}}</ref>\n\n== Civil Society/ Third Sector of Society ==\nDescribed as [[Civil society|\u2018the third sector\u2019]] of society, civil society is the main focus and target of CIVICUS. Its main projects and programmes are aimed at [https://www.alliancemagazine.org/feature/getting-a-world-alliance-started-my-four-years-at-civicus/ strengthening and serving civil society] especially in the Global South. On its website, CIVICUS [https://www.civicus.org/index.php/who-we-are/about-civicus describes] civil society as broad and that it \u201ccovers non-governmental organisations, activists, civil society coalitions and networks, protest and social movements, voluntary bodies, campaigning organisations, charities, faith-based groups, trade unions and philanthropic foundations.\u201d These groups, individuals and organisations make up the CIVICUS membership.\n\n==Activities==\nIn service of its mission and values, the organisation's primary areas of activity are: \n* The '''State of Civil Society Report''' assesses the operating environments for NGOs, [[global governance]] and legislative trends affecting [[civil liberties]].<ref>{{cite web|title=State of Civil Society Report 2014|url=http://civicus.org/images/stories/SOCS%202014.pdf|website=civicus.org/|publisher=CIVICUS|accessdate=7 December 2014}}</ref>\n*'''[https://www.civicus.org/icsw/ International Civil Society Week]''' is a semi-annual global gathering for civil society to connect, debate and create shared solutions. Participation rates range from 500\u20131,000 delegates.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gradjanske.org/en/category/icsw-2019-en/|title=Gra\u0111anske Inicijative {{!}} ICSW 2019|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-18}}</ref>\n*'''[[Goalkeeper-Gate Foundation|Goalkeepers]] Youth Action Accelerator:''' campaign dedicated to accelerating progress towards the U.N. Sustainable Development Goals.\n*'''[http://www.balkancsd.net/affinity-group-for-national-associations-regional-meetings-held-in-johanessbourg/ Affinity Group for National Associations] (AGNA):''' a network that brings together national associations and regional platforms.\n*'''[https://www.civicus.org/index.php/what-we-do/strengthen/civicus-youth CIVICUS Youth]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bushcenter.org/publications/articles/2019/1/goalkeepers/goalkeepers.html|title=The Goalkeepers Youth Action Accelerator is an important investment in our future {{!}} Bush Center|website=The Goalkeepers Youth Action Accelerator is an important investment in our future {{!}} Bush Center|language=en|access-date=2019-12-18}}</ref>:''' connects young activists and encourages youth capacity.\n*'''[https://www.counterpart.org/projects/innovation-for-change/ Innovation 4 Change]:''' a global network of people and organisations working together to protect civic space.\n*'''[https://civicspacewatch.eu/civil-society-accountability-in-times-of-declining-trust-civicuss-journey/ Resilient Roots]:''' The Resilient Roots initiative tests whether organisations who are more accountable and responsive to their primary constituents are more resilient against external threats.\n*'''[https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=855971601426278&ref=br_rs Diversity & Inclusion Group for Networking and Action] (DIGNA):''' a group that brings together change-makers and thought leaders interested in the inclusivity and diversity of civil society.\n*'''[http://monitor.civicus.org CIVICUS Monitor]:''' is a global research tool created and run by over 20 research partners. It tracks changes in civil society across the world and [http://sdg.iisd.org/news/civicus-launches-civic-freedom-tracker/ rates the state of civil society freedoms].\n*'''[https://www.togetherwespeak.org/ SPEAK!]:''' provides a platform for people across the world to speak out on the issues that matter most to them.\n\n== Structure and Governance ==\nCIVICUS has approximately 70 members of staff and is led by [[Lysa John]] who replaces [[Dhananjayan Sriskandarajah|Dr Dhananjayan Sriskandarajah]], who led the organisation from January 2013 to December 2018. Previous Secretary Generals of the organisation also include Miklos Marschall (Hungary), [[Kumi Naidoo]] (South Africa) and Ingrid Srinath (India)\n\nThe governing body of CIVICUS is an International Board of 13 civil society leaders from 13 countries.<ref>{{cite web|title=Board of Directors|url=http://civicus.org/index.php/en/about-us-125/board|website=www.civicus.org|publisher=CIVICUS|accessdate=11 December 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140603211517/http://civicus.org/index.php/en/about-us-125/board|archive-date=3 June 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Funding==\nRevenue to support the operations of CIVICUS is derived from multiple sources, including institutional funders, individual contributions, membership fees, and registration fees for the CIVICUS World Assembly. Aggregated income from 2017/2018 was roughly US$9.6 million.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.civicus.org/documents/reports-and-publications/annual-reports/annual-report-2018-en.pdf|title=CIVICUS ANNUAL REPORT 2017\u20132018|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017/2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.civicus.org/documents/reports-and-publications/annual-reports/annual-report-2018-en.pdf|title=CIVICUS ANNUAL REPORT 2017/2018|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>,CIVICUS received funding for its projects and core support, from the [https://www.government.nl/topics/development-cooperation/the-development-policy-of-the-netherlands Dutch Ministry of Foreign Affairs], the [https://www.sida.se/English Swedish International Development Cooperation Agency], [https://www.fordfoundation.org/ Ford Foundation] and the [https://ec.europa.eu/ European Commission].\n\n==Milestones==\nSince its establishment in 1993, CIVICUS has built successively on its core programmatic activities.\n\n* '''1994:''' Production of first regional reports on the state of civil society.\n* '''1995:''' First World Assembly in Mexico City<ref>{{Citation|last=|first=|title=Participedia|url=https://participedia.net/case/65|work=Wikipedia|volume=|pages=|language=en}}</ref>. The organisation has later gone on to hold 10 World Assemblies which have brought together thousands of activists to discuss and take action on the most pressing issues affecting civil society.\n* '''2000:''' [[Kumi Naidoo]] joins CIVICUS as Secretary General.\n* '''2001-2002:''' Pilot phase of the Civil Society Index (CSI) analyses the state of civil society across a wide range of countries. Since its inception this research project has engaged thousands of stakeholders to exchange information across a total of 75 countries<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.civicus.org/images/stories/AnnualReport_2013_CIVICUS-FINAL.pdf|title=CIVICUS ANNUAL REPORT 2013|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>.\n* '''2003:''' Headquarters move from Washington D.C. to Johannesburg, South Africa\n* '''2004:''' Launch of the [[Global Call to Action Against Poverty|Global Call to Action Against Poverty (GCAP)]] with CIVICUS as a key partner.\n* '''2005:''' Organises first [[Nelson Mandela]]- [[Gra\u00e7a Machel]] Innovation Awards to recognize leading achievements of grassroots organisations.\n* '''2011:''' Produces first annual State of Civil Society Report which provides an assessment of the operating environments for NGOs, global governance and legislative trends affecting civil liberties.\n* '''2013/ 2014:''' Start of International Civil Society Week in Johannesburg under the theme \u201cCitizen action. People power\u201d\n* '''2016:''' [https://taskteamcso.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/ICSW2016_ConceptNote_English_FINAL_Jan2016.pdf ICSW in Bogota, Colombia \u201cActive citizens, Accountable Actions\u201d]\n* '''2017:''' CIVICUS Monitor begins rating the state of civic freedoms in 196 countries\n* '''2019:''' [https://taskteamcso.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/ICSW2016_ConceptNote_English_FINAL_Jan2016.pdf ICSW\u00a0 in Belgrade, Serbia: \u201cPower of Togetherness\u201d]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:International non-profit organizations]]\n[[Category:Civil society]]\n[[Category:Organisations based in Johannesburg]]\n[[Category:Non-profit organisations based in South Africa]]\n", "text_old": "{{COI|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox organization\n| name = CIVICUS: World Alliance For Citizen Participation\n| native_name = <!-- Organization's name in its local language -->\n| image = \n| image_size = 300px\n| motto = \n| type = International Non-profit/ Civil Society Organisation<br />INGO/CSO\n| headquarters = [[Johannesburg]], [[South Africa]]\n| services = Membership Alliance\n| leader_title = [[Secretary General]]\n| leader_name = Lysa John\n| homepage = {{URL|civicus.org}}\n}}\n\n\n'''CIVICUS''' is an international non-profit organisation, which describes itself as \u201ca global alliance dedicated to strengthening citizen action and [[civil society]] around the world.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=2014 CIVICUS Annual Report|url=http://civicus.org/AGMSecure/downloads/Annual%20Report_final%20version_sml_2.pdf#page=5|publisher=CIVICUS|accessdate=7 December 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170915034823/http://civicus.org/AGMSecure/downloads/Annual%20Report_final%20version_sml_2.pdf#page=5|archive-date=15 September 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> Founded in 1993, the organisation today counts more than 8500 members in more than 175 countries, with its headquarters in [[Johannesburg]] and offices in Geneva and New York.<ref>{{cite news|title=Calls for Azerbaijan to end crackdown on civil society and uphold Council of Europe Commitments|url=http://www.civicsolidarity.org/article/1033/calls-azerbaijan-end-crackdown-civil-society-and-uphold-council-europe-commitments|accessdate=7 December 2014|publisher=Civic Solidarity}}</ref>\n\n==Brief history==\nIn 1991, an international group of 20 leaders from [[Non governmental organisations|Non-Governmental Organisations (NGOs)]] and social movements met to explore how to support citizen participation in governmental decision-making processes.<ref>{{cite news|title=Getting a world alliance started \u2013 my four years at CIVICUS|url=http://www.alliancemagazine.org/feature/getting-a-world-alliance-started-my-four-years-at-civicus/|accessdate=7 December 2014|publisher=Alliance Magazine}}</ref> This process culminated in 1993 when a founding board established CIVICUS from the Latin term meaning \"of the community\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Reaching across sectors and building bridges|url=http://www.pdac.ca/docs/default-source/publications---communique/reaching-across-sectors-and-building-bridges-(december-2012).pdf?sfvrsn=0|website=www.pdac.ca/|publisher=Prospectors and Developers Association of Canada|accessdate=7 December 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140412112818/http://www.pdac.ca/docs/default-source/publications---communique/reaching-across-sectors-and-building-bridges-(december-2012).pdf?sfvrsn=0|archive-date=12 April 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Mission and Values==\nThe organisation works to protect and grow [[civic space]] where people can express and organise themselves.<ref>{{cite web|title=CIVICUS Our Strategic Priorities 2013- 2017|url=http://civicus.org/images/stories/CIVICUS%20SPs.English.Final.pdf|website=civicus.org/|publisher=CIVICUS|accessdate=7 December 2014}}</ref> In particular, the organisation focuses on regions where [[participatory democracy]] and [[freedom of association]] are at risk.<ref>{{cite web|title=Volunteering and Social Activism|url=http://www.unv.org/fileadmin/img/wvw/latestVolpub.pdf|website=www.unv.org/|publisher=United Nations Volunteers Organisation|accessdate=7 December 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303205556/http://www.unv.org/fileadmin/img/wvw/latestVolpub.pdf|archive-date=3 March 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> CIVICUS counts among its central values: Justice and Equality, where all people are free to exercise their rights as citizens as defined in the [[Universal Declaration of Human Rights]].<ref>{{cite book|title=International Encyclopaedia of Civil Society|publisher=Springer|url=https://www.springer.com/social+sciences/book/978-0-387-93994-0|accessdate=7 December 2014|isbn=9780387939940|date=2009-12-16}}</ref>\n\n== Civil Society/ Third Sector of Society ==\nDescribed as [[Civil society|\u2018the third sector\u2019]] of society, civil society is the main focus and target of CIVICUS. Its main projects and programmes are aimed at [https://www.alliancemagazine.org/feature/getting-a-world-alliance-started-my-four-years-at-civicus/ strengthening and serving civil society] especially in the Global South. On its website, CIVICUS [https://www.civicus.org/index.php/who-we-are/about-civicus describes] civil society as broad and that it \u201ccovers non-governmental organisations, activists, civil society coalitions and networks, protest and social movements, voluntary bodies, campaigning organisations, charities, faith-based groups, trade unions and philanthropic foundations.\u201d These groups, individuals and organisations make up the CIVICUS membership.\n\n==Activities==\nIn service of its mission and values, the organisation\u2019s primary areas of activity are: \n* The '''State of Civil Society Report''' assesses the operating environments for NGOs, [[global governance]] and legislative trends affecting [[civil liberties]].<ref>{{cite web|title=State of Civil Society Report 2014|url=http://civicus.org/images/stories/SOCS%202014.pdf|website=civicus.org/|publisher=CIVICUS|accessdate=7 December 2014}}</ref>\n*'''[https://www.civicus.org/icsw/ International Civil Society Week]''' is a semi-annual global gathering for civil society to connect, debate and create shared solutions. Participation rates range from 500-1,000 delegates.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gradjanske.org/en/category/icsw-2019-en/|title=Gra\u0111anske Inicijative {{!}} ICSW 2019|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-18}}</ref>\n*'''[[Goalkeeper-Gate Foundation|Goalkeepers]] Youth Action Accelerator:''' campaign dedicated to accelerating progress towards the U.N. Sustainable Development Goals.\n*'''[http://www.balkancsd.net/affinity-group-for-national-associations-regional-meetings-held-in-johanessbourg/ Affinity Group for National Associations] (AGNA):''' a network that brings together national associations and regional platforms.\n*'''[https://www.civicus.org/index.php/what-we-do/strengthen/civicus-youth CIVICUS Youth]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bushcenter.org/publications/articles/2019/1/goalkeepers/goalkeepers.html|title=The Goalkeepers Youth Action Accelerator is an important investment in our future {{!}} Bush Center|website=The Goalkeepers Youth Action Accelerator is an important investment in our future {{!}} Bush Center|language=en|access-date=2019-12-18}}</ref>:''' connects young activists and encourages youth capacity.\n*'''[https://www.counterpart.org/projects/innovation-for-change/ Innovation 4 Change]:''' a global network of people and organisations working together to protect civic space.\n*'''[https://civicspacewatch.eu/civil-society-accountability-in-times-of-declining-trust-civicuss-journey/ Resilient Roots]:''' The Resilient Roots initiative tests whether organisations who are more accountable and responsive to their primary constituents are more resilient against external threats.\n*'''[https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=855971601426278&ref=br_rs Diversity & Inclusion Group for Networking and Action] (DIGNA):''' a group that brings together change-makers and thought leaders interested in the inclusivity and diversity of civil society.\n*'''[http://monitor.civicus.org CIVICUS Monitor]:''' is a global research tool created and run by over 20 research partners. It tracks changes in civil society across the world and [http://sdg.iisd.org/news/civicus-launches-civic-freedom-tracker/ rates the state of civil society freedoms].\n*'''[https://www.togetherwespeak.org/ SPEAK!]:''' provides a platform for people across the world to speak out on the issues that matter most to them.\n\n== Structure and Governance ==\nCIVICUS has approximately 70 members of staff and is led by [[Lysa John]] who replaces [[Dhananjayan Sriskandarajah|Dr Dhananjayan Sriskandarajah]], who led the organisation from January 2013 to December 2018. Previous Secretary Generals of the organisation also include Miklos Marschall (Hungary), [[Kumi Naidoo]] (South Africa) and Ingrid Srinath (India)\n\nThe governing body of CIVICUS is an International Board of 13 civil society leaders from 13 countries.<ref>{{cite web|title=Board of Directors|url=http://civicus.org/index.php/en/about-us-125/board|website=www.civicus.org|publisher=CIVICUS|accessdate=11 December 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140603211517/http://civicus.org/index.php/en/about-us-125/board|archive-date=3 June 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Funding==\nRevenue to support the operations of CIVICUS is derived from multiple sources, including institutional funders, individual contributions, membership fees, and registration fees for the CIVICUS World Assembly. Aggregated income from 2017/2018 was roughly $9.6 million USD.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.civicus.org/documents/reports-and-publications/annual-reports/annual-report-2018-en.pdf|title=CIVICUS ANNUAL REPORT 2017\u20132018|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017/2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.civicus.org/documents/reports-and-publications/annual-reports/annual-report-2018-en.pdf|title=CIVICUS ANNUAL REPORT 2017/2018|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>,CIVICUS received funding for its projects and core support, from the [https://www.government.nl/topics/development-cooperation/the-development-policy-of-the-netherlands Dutch Ministry of Foreign Affairs], the [https://www.sida.se/English Swedish International Development Cooperation Agency], [https://www.fordfoundation.org/ Ford Foundation] and the [https://ec.europa.eu/ European Commission].\n\n==Milestones==\nSince its establishment in 1993, CIVICUS has built successively on its core programmatic activities.\n\n* '''1994:''' Production of first regional reports on the state of civil society.\n* '''1995:''' First World Assembly in Mexico City<ref>{{Citation|last=|first=|title=Participedia|url=https://participedia.net/case/65|work=Wikipedia|volume=|pages=|language=en}}</ref>. The organisation has later gone on to hold 10 World Assemblies which have brought together thousands of activists to discuss and take action on the most pressing issues affecting civil society.\n* '''2000:''' [[Kumi Naidoo]] joins CIVICUS as Secretary General.\n* '''2001-2002:''' Pilot phase of the Civil Society Index (CSI) analyses the state of civil society across a wide range of countries. Since its inception this research project has engaged thousands of stakeholders to exchange information across a total of 75 countries<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.civicus.org/images/stories/AnnualReport_2013_CIVICUS-FINAL.pdf|title=CIVICUS ANNUAL REPORT 2013|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>.\n* '''2003:''' Headquarters move from Washington D.C. to Johannesburg, South Africa\n* '''2004:''' Launch of the [[Global Call to Action Against Poverty|Global Call to Action Against Poverty (GCAP)]] with CIVICUS as a key partner.\n* '''2005:''' Organises first [[Nelson Mandela]]- [[Gra\u00e7a Machel]] Innovation Awards to recognize leading achievements of grassroots organisations.\n* '''2011:''' Produces first annual State of Civil Society Report which provides an assessment of the operating environments for NGOs, global governance and legislative trends affecting civil liberties.\n* '''2013/ 2014:''' Start of International Civil Society Week in Johannesburg under the theme \u201cCitizen action. People power\u201d\n* '''2016:''' [https://taskteamcso.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/ICSW2016_ConceptNote_English_FINAL_Jan2016.pdf ICSW in Bogota, Colombia \u201cActive citizens, Accountable Actions\u201d]\n* '''2017:''' CIVICUS Monitor begins rating the state of civic freedoms in 196 countries\n* '''2019:''' [https://taskteamcso.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/ICSW2016_ConceptNote_English_FINAL_Jan2016.pdf ICSW\u00a0 in Belgrade, Serbia: \u201cPower of Togetherness\u201d]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:International non-profit organizations]]\n[[Category:Civil society]]\n[[Category:Organisations based in Johannesburg]]\n[[Category:Non-profit organisations based in South Africa]]\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: $9.6 million USD \u2192  US$9.6 million, \u2019s \u2192 's, 500-1 \u2192 500\u20131", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Civicus"}
